                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Governor
                            <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Italian ambassador inquires what progress has been made by the State
                    authorities in the investigation of the lynching of Italians at Tallulah. The
                    President requests me to express to you the gratification it would afford him to
                    be enabled to assure the ambassador, what he can not doubt, that the justice of
                    the State proves potential for the pursuit and punishment of the offenders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
